<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Sthaz</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Nov 2001<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>/applaud<br />
<br />
This is a *great* post and pretty much sums up a lot of other ideas floating around in this forum as well as effectively tackling one of the most common complaints of the shaman community, 'Fix Alchemy.'  While I agree with the majority, I have a few points I take issue with or would expect others to.<br />
<br />
Ress potions.  While I think this would be an extremely useful addition, I just don't think it's ability shaman should have.  Some feel that clerics already lost alot of their day to day utility in the Incomplete Heals that just went in (not my opinion, see other threads).  I think this would only further that opinion.  No, clerics will NEVER be useless, but farming out their abilities to other classes is a little unfair I think.  Maybe.... just MAYBE, a revive potions of some sort that didn't prohibit an exp ress later would be in order.<br />
<br />
Shaman forage?  Erm, Iksar already have this.  Not to be petty, and I'm NOT trying to get into a debate on which race is the better shaman, but if this racial ability is handed out to the whole class, shouldn't they be compensated in some way?  <br />
<br />
Gate potions, while I think the revisions you've posted are necessary, I honestly think they should be cheaper to make.  Why?  I know a guy who 2boxes a 60 shaman and 60 warrior.  He uses Thurg potions despite a high skill in alchemy because stocking up on ingedients is cheaper/easier then supplying alchemy made ones to his warrior (and the location is more appealing) and this guy has absolutely no problems generating a lot of money when he wants it.<br />
<br />
Mana regen potions, again, I fully support your proposed revisions, but I doubt the enchanter community would go for it.  While I like them depending on chanter made ingredients, I can't help but predict those vials of mana would skyrocket in price in the bazaar.  Shaman being able to effectively 'cast' KEI just isn't right (tho I sure wish we could!).<br />
<br />
Illusion potions should be illusions only, imho.  Just seems a little too much otherwise.  No faction, no bonus, just a toy to keep it interesting.  Make em lore and/or do drop to limit usage (tho I'd love to have gnome rangers out there for sac to the loot gods).  I'd still make em with no bonus, and I know folks who would buy them at 100pp or so apiece if they were tradable.<br />
<br />
MOST importantly, which you mentioned and I fully and totally agree with, make availability the limiting factor.  Stop making alchemy depend on your bank account, there's MUCH better things to spend hard earned pp on (see high level kunark spell drop rates).  Make mob drops and ground spawn, or other tradeskill items, part of the process.<br />
<br />
I'm a shaman who would very very much like to master alchemy, simply because it's part of our class identity, but at present, there's just no motivation to spend the money.<br />
<br />
Here's hoping at least some part of our input goes in...<br />
<br />
Sthaz<br />
Oracle<br />
Succoring Winds<br />
Bristlebane</p>
	
	
	
	
	
