	<p>I like these proposed changes a lot. <br />
<br />
 We all know prices are ridiculous. Above all verant has to do something to reduce the price on the herbs, or give us more return on our investment when we sell them to vendors. <br />
 I'd also love to see the trivials spread out a little better. They've done this well with pottery, baking, and other skills; they can do the same with Alchemy.<br />
 I love the idea of foraging. I think it would add a great deal to Alchemy, AND it would be a benefit to ALL shamans, including Iksar. I don't feel Iksar would need to be compensated because they would have the cap raised on their foraging. Just because they could forage some before doesn't mean they would not benefit from greater skill at it. <br />
 Another idea would be to make the herbs foragable, but NOT give shamans foraging skill. We would have to rely on the Bazaar and the player market to buy our herbs. OMG! Pay druids and rangers for our herbs? Why not? &lt;Shrug&gt; We'd be paying them for a service. It's possible (probable unfortunately) that certain individuals would try to hurt us by selling them ridiculously high in price, but I think the general market would undercut them and force the prices down. If not, make some friends who can forage and work out deals with them. <br />
 Yes in this case Iksar shaman would have a HUGE advantage. SO, I guess the rest of us would have to be asking what WE get because of that. Not to be petty of course <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="wink" smilieid="5" /><br />
 Seriously the answer is simple, foraging alchemy herbs would probably trivial far beyond the skill level that an Iksar's inate foraging is set at. They might be able to luck into a few now and then, but would have to buy most of them like any other shaman.<br />
 If you simply can't stand the idea of relying on someone else for your herbs, than just accept the current vendor driven rubish. Can't have it both ways. I personaly would rather see a player make some money from my purchase rather than dumping it on an NPC.<br />
 I'm honestly not sure why Stat potions don't sell considering the number of people who ask me to buff them with Str or Dex or whatever. I guess it's okay to ask for someone to cast a spell for free, but heck no am I going to pay for some dumb potion. &lt;Sigh&gt; Do people not like the negative effects that come with them? Who knows?<br />
 I'm personally convinced that most of our potions won't sell on traders in the Bazaar because noone knows what they do. How many people out there know that Blood of the Wolf is a SoW potion. Of course we do, but do our buyers? Do they know what blistering flesh is? Purity? If they don't know what it is why would they buy it? One thing I'd like to see in a revamp is clearer descriptions. Example, put &quot;Dammage Shield&quot; as the effect, not &quot;Blistering Flesh&quot;.<br />
 For new utility potions, some of these ideas seem good.<br />
 First of all I agree that Illusion potions should be just that, Illusion. Adding Lich and Archlich effects would drive necro's into a frenzy and rightfully so. That's they're area, let them keep it.<br />
 I don't see the need for stat changes either. If you want stat changes use those stat potions that seem so useless. It doesn't make sense to me to add stats to another potion when we could be trying to sell the stat potions we already have.<br />
 As for the Mind potions, I'd say no to KEI. That would take too much away from enchanters. Same with Rez potions and clerics. I'd never want to see a rez potion, no matter how long the recovery time is. They very fact that people WILL run all the way back to Nexus and the Bazaar and pay Enchanters 100 plat for KEI is a wonderful thing. I personally feel it's wrong to take that away from them. Its too bad people won't pay for Focus like that <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
<br />
 Still for the most part the ideas here ARE excellent and I would love to see a revamp of alchemy done sometime soon.<br />
<br />
Korginard Wintersfury<br />
58 Shaman<br />
Innoruuk</p>
	
	
	
	
	
