	<!-- message -->
	<p>Great post <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
<br />
I agree on almost everything. The KEI potions would be great as well as the rez one although I'd say 90% max on the rez potion (one you listed is 96%?). I think they'd really give us a reason to work on alchemy, however I think they should be triv &gt;255. I know chanters and clerics would both be angry at first but think about how many people would actually reliably be able to make them. Plus I think it would be in line with the good things people can make with the other tradeskills (I REALLY wish I knew a grandmaster Tribunal smith /drool Artificer's Ringmail).<br />
<br />
Only thing I disagree with are a few of the complexity thing. <blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />- Items created by other tradeskills (brewing, baking, etc.) <br />
- Enchanted items from Enchanters (vials of mana, etc.) <br />
- Various summoned items (from Mages, Necros, etc.) <br />
- Foraged items (Herbs, Zone Essences, etc.) <br />
- Herbs that need to be Imbued or Enchanted in order to form the potion - Add a spell for doing this to our book <br />
- Ground spawns <br />
- Looted items<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Foraged items. Unless we get foraging as a skill nuh uh. I don't mind interdependancy but foraging is really boring and I really don't want ask friends to waste their time doing it for me. And no I'm not starting over at level one as an Ikky <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="" title="stick out tongue" smilieid="6" /><br />
<br />
Ground spawns. Eh /shrug ok as long as it's not some once a day in one spot spawn kinda thing. If all I have to do is go to a zone and spend some time running around looking for the things on the ground I'd have no problem with it and would readily go along with it. <br />
<br />
Enchanted/imbued/summoned items Good call <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
<br />
Looted items. No, no no no no no no no........<b>NO</b> <img src="images/smilies/mad.gif" border="0" alt="" title="mad" smilieid="9" /> . I did Smithing.....until I had to farm greens. I thought about doing tailoring.....until I found out it involves WAY too much farming of greens. The very reason I LOVE alchemy is in almost every potion no <b>boring</b> mind-numbing slaughtering of poor unoffensive little green mobs involved.<br />
<br />
Only correction is there are indeed no component levitation and EB potions. I farmed enough just to see if the recipies did indeed work. For EB you need a Froglok Leg (from Guk)+Sea Spirit (sold in Shar Vahl in the shaman guild) and for the lev you need a lightstone (from willowhisps)+Figwort(again from Shar Vahl in Shaman guild). They're a pain because of the farming but they do indeed exist. Not sure on their triv but it's below 117.<br />
<br />
Anyways again great post, very well thought out <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
