	<!-- message -->
	<p>I doubt we would ever see res potions, if right click ressing was supposed to be so easy they would never have changed the buy back on staff of forbiden rites to 225,000pp<br />
<br />
Increasing the buy back costs on potions would not fix alchemy, it would only help you max the skill it would not help you sell the potions. Lowering the cost to make potions would be the only really way to help fix alchemy. And adding more useful potions with no negative stats would also be good.<br />
<br />
As for KEI potions, i would have to say no way, we would be infringing on enchanters far to much. <br />
<br />
As for foraged/ground spawn items this could be a good thing yet also very bad(Iksars would really like the foraged components). But take a look in the bazaar and check the prices on some of the basic stuff like spider silks, that are going for upto 10pp on some servers. Alchemy would end up being even more expensive to raise. <br />
<br />
Enchanters already have one of the biggest strangle holds on tradeskills why give them another one? After all alchemy is practiced by shamen that belong to simplistic/tribal cultures having them run off to another city to find an enchanter just seems daft. So i would have to say that mana vials is a bad idea and should not be included. Unless illusion potions were added then having enchanters as part of proccess would be a good thing.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
